'''Sri Venkateswara College of Engineering (SVCE) ''' (to be conferred University status) is a [[private]] [[college]] located in ''Pennalur'' , [[Sriperumbudur]] near [[Chennai]].
SVCE was founded by the Sri Venkateswara Educational and Health Trust (SVEHT) in the year 1985. The Trust was founded on August 1, 1984 at the behest of Sri [[Jayendra Saraswathi]] Swamigal.The college, established in the city of [[Chennai]] by the [[SPIC]] group, a prominent petro-chemical corporation in India, is said to be among the top three colleges<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.india-inc.in/DR-A.-C.-MUTHIAH.html
 | title = SVCE in top three Tamil Nadu colleges,see end paragraphs
 | publisher = http://www.india-inc.in
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year = 2007
 | accessdate = 2008-05-06
}}</ref>  in Tamil Nadu, and a Tier-I institution among self financing colleges.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/thscrip/print.pl?file=2007080460550800.htm&date=2007/08/04/&prd=th&
 | title = SVCE considered a Tier-I institution;see "Intense competition"
 | publisher = The Hindu
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year = 2007
 | accessdate = 2008-04-19
}}</ref> 

SVCE's founding objective was to plan and implement a programme of education in Engineering and Allied Sciences, to promote research, disseminate knowledge and to foster the cooperation and exchange of ideas between the academic community and industrial organizations and to develop entrepreneurship skills among students.

== History ==
[[Image:Svceoldcamp.jpg|thumb|right|125px|Inauguration of the old college campus;April 8, 1985]]
===Initial Years===
In November 1984 the college was granted permission to conduct Engineering courses in the disciplines of [[Mechanical Engineering]], [[Electronics and Communication Engineering]] and [[Computer Science Engineering]], awarded by the [[University of Madras]].

The college complex at Nazarathpet (near [[Poonamallee]]) was inaugurated on April 8, 1985 by Sri [http://www.tnrajbhavan.gov.in/images/PastGov/SLKhurana.JPG S.L Khurana], former [[Governor]] of [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url =http://www.svce.ac.in/about/past.html
 | title =  History and Milestones of SVCE 
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =2007
 | accessdate =2008-05-06
}}</ref>

===Expansion===
[[Image:SVCE entrance close up.jpg|thumb|left|The entrance to the college]]
In 1991, the college shifted into its new campus at [[Pennalur]], near the town of [[Sriperumbudur]]. The buildings were designed by the architect P.T.Krishnan. The ''[[grihapravesam]]'' function of the new Campus was performed on July 25,1991 in the presence of  Sri [[Jayendra Saraswathi]] Swamigal,and was inaugurated by Shri R.Venketaraman(Former President of [[India]]) on January 5,1992,and received approval from the [[All India Council for Technical Education]] the same year.Courses in [[Electrical & Electronics Engineering]] and [[Chemical Engineering]] Courses were started in 1994.[[Sri_Venkateswara_College_of_Engineering#cite_note-2|<sup>[3]</sup>]]

The college celebrated its decennial on 16-3-1995 in the presence of former Minister of State for Commerce and present [[Finance minister]] of the Government of India Shri [[P. Chidambaram]].In 1996 the college initiated a course in [[Information Technology]],and was the ''first college in the country'' to do so.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/department/it/index.html
 | title = First to introduce a B Tech Degree program in Information Technology
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-03-11
}}</ref>The college obtained an [[ISO 9001:2000]] certification in 2002.[[Sri_Venkateswara_College_of_Engineering#cite_note-2|<sup>[3]</sup>]]

===Challenges and controversies===
[[Image:Svceadmin.JPG|thumb|175px|SVCE's main block,which houses the library & administration block.]]
SVCE went under the government scanner with the Directorate of Technical Education(DOTE) intensifying its drive against the collection of capitation fee and tuition fee in excess of that prescribed.

It was found that a donation of {{INRConvert|500000}} was allegedly paid by a student through a demand draft to the Spic Educational Trust. DOTE officials are said to have found that the trust was an unregistered entity and traced its bank account, which was supposedly linked to the college. DOTE officials claimed they would initiate legal action against the college and also ask the [[AICTE]] to cancel its recognition in the forthcoming academic year.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url =http://www.hindu.com/2007/07/31/stories/2007073154040600.htm
 | title =  Surprise checks at 142 self-financing engineering colleges in Tamil Nadu 
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =2007
 | accessdate =2008-04-22
}}</ref>

The crackdown by the Directorate of Technical Education officials on the college did not however,stop the filling up of its seats under the single window system in the first few days of the 2007 DOTE counselling.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.hinduonnet.com/thehindu/thscrip/print.pl?file=2007080460550800.htm&date=2007/08/04/&prd=th&
 | title = crackdown by the Directorate of Technical Education has not applied the brakes;see "Intense competition"
 | publisher = The Hindu
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year = 2007
 | accessdate = 2008-04-19
}}</ref>

==Facilities==
===Library===
SVCE has a {{convert|1338|m2|sqft|-2|sing=on}} well established, fully computerized library spanning three floors with over 21,000 titles covering major fields of Science and Engineering, a conference room, an ample study space and a seating capacity of over 200.The ground floor is Air-conditioned,with conferencing, multimedia, internet, reprography facilities, a CD-ROM collection and a book bank for deserving students.
[[Image:SVCE library panorama.jpg|400px|right|thumb|The centrally air conditioned central library]]
The college subscribes to most major technical journals including the [[IEEE]], ACM and ASME journals.Over 59,000 volumes and 200 CD's are available,and around 400 print and online journals are subscribed.

Apart from the central library, all departments maintain their own departmental libraries.SVCE is an institutional member of The British Council Library, [[IIT Madras]], American Council Library, [http://delnet.nic.in/  DELNET] and [http://www.angelfire.com/in/malibnet/genesis.html  MALIBNET]<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/department/nonac/lib.html
 | title = Library details
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-04-20
}}</ref>.The library uses multimedia computers with internet connectivity,[[CBT]],CDs,e-books and e-journals to promote e-learning.

A library committee headed by the Principal, comprising of all the Heads of Departments,and Student Representatives,meet every semester to discuss the functioning of the library.

