===Sports and athletic facilities===
[[Image:SVCE cricket ground panorama.jpg<U+200E>|350px|thumb|right|A match in progress at the cricket ground]]

The {{convert|15|acre|sqft|1}} facility has a [[swimming pool]], synthetic and clay tennis courts, turf cricket ground, basketball, football grounds, ball badminton, volley ball courts and a 400 meter track for athletics.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/department/nonac/facilities.html
 | title = College sports facilities
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-04-22
}}</ref>

{{convert|350|m2|sqft|-2|sing=on}} is dedicated to a [[table tennis]] hall, [[gym]]nasium, and [[carom]] and [[chess]] rooms.

Students are encouraged to participate in intramural,extramural and the ''Tamil Nadu Inter Engineering Sports ''(TIES) competitions. The College conducts inter-college tournaments in [[basketball]],[[volleyball]], [[cricket]] and [[ball badminton]].
[[Image:Medical Centre.JPG|175px|right|thumb|The newly constructed medical center]]
===Medical Center===
The campus houses a newly constructed medical center near the [[Sri_Venkateswara_College_of_Engineering#Housing|hostel blocks]],with a nurse and doctor available round the clock to attend to any emergencies.

===Entrepreneurship Development Cell===
The Entrepreneurship Development Cell was formed in 1996, and has organized a number of awareness camps in the last 10 years to motivate students to become entrepreneurs.
Today this Development cell is one of its kind in Tamilnadu<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/department/nonac/edc/profile.htm
 | title = First EDC in Tamilnadu
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-04-22
}}</ref> and one among 20 in the country.

The objective of this cell is to motivate and train students towards Science and Technology so that students ''become job creators rather than job seekers''.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/department/nonac/edc/profile.htm
 | title = Job creators rather than job seekers
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-04-19
}}</ref>

===Transport===
<center>{{wide image|SVCE bus fleet panorama.jpg|1000px|A panoramic view of the svce bus fleet}}</center>

Since the campus is located {{convert|35|km|mi|1}} away from [[Chennai]] city,transportation is provided between various parts of [[Chennai]] city and the college.Initially the college started out with eight buses,and now run over 50.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url =http://www.svce.ac.in/department/nonac/trans.html
 | title = Transport details
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate =2008-04-22
}}</ref>
Buses are operated on Saturdays and Sundays for special classes,[[NCC]], Sports etc. On special occasions buses are sent for industrial visits and social service activities.The College owns four of the buses,one ambulance and a van.

A transport committee headed by a convener takes care of the smooth operation of buses.A staff member in charge of the bus (one teaching and one supporting) also ensure the smooth functioning of the buses.

==Student Life==
====Housing====
[[Image:SVCE walkway fisheye.jpg|250px|right|thumb|Buildings inside the college]]
[[Image:swimming pool-svce campus.JPG|250px|thumb|The [[swimming pool]]]]
The SVCE [[dormitory]] housing comprise of five independent blocks. The first block was built and inaugurated in 1998. The second in December 1999,the third in August 2001 and the fourth block in August 2003. All the four blocks together accommodate 500 boys. A fifth block for girls was built and inaugurated in October 2002,housing 100 girls.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url = http://www.svce.ac.in/campus/hostel/index.html
 | title = Hostel detail
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate = 2008-04-22
}}</ref>
In view of a high demand for housing, two more new dormitory blocks are under construction.

====Scholarships and Awards====
In 2004,the [[chairman]] and governing council initiated a scheme that would distribute 5% of the total college tuition fee income to students as a full semester scholarship,and as prizes to top scorers in college tests and university examinations.Gold medals are awarded to the top 10 university rank holders,and a silver medal is awarded to the college first rank holder.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia
 | url =http://www.svce.ac.in/admission/
 | title =  Scholarships and Honors
 | publisher = SVCE website
 | encyclopedia = 
 | year =
 | accessdate =2008-04-22
}}</ref>Other notable awards include the Outstanding Undergraduate student Award,Outstanding Sports person Award and the Best Student Award by the Indian Society for Technical Education.
{| style='float:center;font-size: 80%;border:1px solid #dddddd; background-color:#fefefe; padding:3px;margin:1em'
|
Students are given a full semester scholarship on the basis of: <br />
<div class="references-2column">
*Merit
*Merit and Economic Means
*Economic Means
*Sports
*NCC</div>
